A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 2 of Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to university system, so as to require the possession of opioid antagonists
3 by institutions within the University System of Georgia; to amend Article 2 of Chapter 4 of
4 Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to technical and adult education,
5 so as to require the possession of opioid antagonists by units within the Technical College
6 System of Georgia; to provide for definitions; to provide for possession of opioid antagonists
7 by certain individuals; to require the maintenance of a stock supply of opioid antagonists; to
8 provide for the use and location of opioid antagonist storage compartments; to authorize
9 trained personnel to administer opioid antagonists and carry opioid antagonists; on their
10 person; to provide for immunity; to provide that neither civil liability nor professional
11 discipline shall accrue to personnel, the systems, or institutions or units thereof; to provide
12 for an exception; to provide for activation of the emergency medical services system and
13 notification of emergency contacts; to provide for a community funding source contingency;
14 to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
