16 SECTION 1.
17 Part 2 of Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
18 relating to university system, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
19 "20-3-88.
20 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
21 (1) 'Automated external defibrillator' means a defibrillator which:
22 (A) Is capable of cardiac rhythm analysis;
23 (B) Will charge and be capable of being activated to deliver a countershock after
24 electrically detecting the presence of certain cardiac dysrhythmias; and
25 (C) Is capable of continuous recording of the cardiac dysrhythmia at the scene with a
26 mechanism for transfer and storage or for printing for review subsequent to use.
27 (2) 'Community funding source' means local sources of capital provided by local banking
28 institutions, including credit unions, community foundations, county or municipal
29 governments, businesses, or residents.
30 (3) 'Institution' means any college, school, academy, university, or experiment station at
31 any particular location which forms a part of the university system.
32 (4) 'Opioid antagonist' means a drug that binds to opioid receptors and blocks or inhibits
33 the effect of opioids acting on those receptors, including, but not limited to, naloxone,
34 hydrochloride, or any other similarly acting drug that is approved by the federal Food and
35 Drug Administration for the treatment of an opioid related overdose.
36 (5) 'Opioid antagonist storage compartment' means the structure in which opioid
37 antagonists may be stored.
38 (6) 'University system' means the University System of Georgia.
39 (b) No student, visitor, or university system employee shall be prohibited from possessing
40 an opioid antagonist on university system property or at a university system sponsored
41 activity.
