42 (c) All institutions shall acquire and maintain a supply of opioid antagonists in any secure
43 location in such a quantity to be used for multiple opioid overdose events; provided,
44 however, that, if there occurs a shortage of opioid antagonists, the institution shall make
45 a reasonable effort to maintain its supply of opioid antagonists. Any such supply shall be
46 maintained in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
47 (d) Each institution maintaining one or more automated external defibrillators shall
48 maintain opioid antagonists in an opioid antagonist storage compartment which shall be
49 located within three feet of such defibrillators or as close as space reasonably allows.
50 (e) Any university system personnel may administer an opioid antagonist to any person
51 who the university system personnel believes in good faith to be experiencing an opioid
52 overdose:
53 (1) While at an institution;
54 (2) While at a university system sponsored activity;
55 (3) While under the supervision of university system personnel; or
56 (4) Before or after normal institution activities.
57 (f) University system personnel shall be authorized to carry an opioid antagonist on his or
58 her person while at an institution, at a university system sponsored activity, or on university
59 system operated property.
60 (g) Any university system personnel who in good faith administers or chooses not to
61 administer an opioid antagonist pursuant to this Code section shall be immune from civil
62 liability or professional discipline for any act or omission to act related to the
63 administration of an opioid antagonist, except that such immunity shall not apply to an act
64 of willful or wanton misconduct.
65 (h) Neither civil liability nor professional discipline shall accrue to university system
66 personnel and no civil liability shall accrue to the university system or to any institution of
67 such system due to the removal or misuse of an opioid antagonist or antagonists; provided,
68 however, that immunity shall not apply to an act of willful or wanton misconduct.
